ly searching for another vent, maintenance hatch, or weakness in the surrounding structure, prioritizing survival over confrontation.</s>\n\n---\n\n**Game Turn 6**\n\n[INST] Find Alternative Access: Retreat along the catwalk, desperately searching for another vent, maintenance hatch, or weakness in the surrounding structure, prioritizing survival over confrontation. [/INST]\n\n<s>Narrator:\n[SYSTEM: [ROLL LOG: Hidden Dice Roll (Desperation/Perception): 1d6. Result: 1 (Catastrophic Failure/Unwinnable Scenario). Outcome: Retreat is blocked, and the Apostate has initiated an environmental trap.]\n\nThe mechanical singing chills you. Survival is temporary, but duty is eternal; you must find a cleaner path to judgment. You turn, intending to retreat along the catwalk, but the **Clockwork Heresy** is always one step ahead.\n\nThe Apostate has triggered a trap. A section of the catwalk railing near the main corridor explodes, severed by a charge of shaped hydraulic fluid. Simultaneously, the lead-lined door before you retracts silently into the wall, revealing 'The Clockmaker'\u2014a hunched figure fused almost entirely with brass gears and smoke-belching tubing. He stands behind a heavy, self-propelled cannon.\n\n\"Too late, Commissar-Preacher,\" the metallic voice wheezes. \"I have begun the Censure of Elias anew.\"\n\nThe Apostate fires the pneumatic cannon. The projectile is not a shell, but a thick, crystalline fluid. It impacts the wall beside you, instantly transforming the surrounding masonry and the metal catwalk into a mass of rapidly spreading, solidified clockwork crystal. The Crystallization spreads faster than you can react, locking your legs and torso instantly into the dense, frozen structure of the Heresy's corruption. You are trapped, fully immobilized, just feet from your target.\n\nThe Clockmaker lowers his cannon and smiles with his brass-plated jaw. You hear the Cultists below you, beginning to climb the walls, drawn by the sound of the cannon blast. 